So how do I feel turning 44?

Like most grown men, it's 100% about respecting and valuing my remaining time.

Tighten your circle to people who see the same vision and shared interests.  Only do things that truly contribute value or you find a LOT of fun.

Yes, I have more energy, focus and drive than ever.  But I understand that it has a limited time.

For people who use their brains to do what they do, these are the years where you're at an intersection between having the physical stamina to move mountains, and years of experience to produce your best work. 

40's and 50's are really the years your legacy is carved out, and you get to leave your mark on the world.

It's also important to have as much fun as possible.

Do those hardcore insane yikes, ski every mountain, do anything physical you wanted to do.

So just been cranking that out, and excited for you to see what's coming.

Have a lot of truly insane projects in the works, many near completion.
